+# OpenSpec Change Proposal: `add-difficulty-metrics`
+
+## Summary
+
+Add a *learning system* observer, `massgen.learning.DifficultyMetricsObserver`,
+that consumes the coordination tracker's existing `AgentAnswer` and
+`AgentVote` records and emits four interpretable metrics — Agent Confidence
+Entropy (ACE), Critique Severity Dispersion (CSD), Winner Flip Rate (WFR),
+and a composite Task Difficulty Index (TDI) — per round and per run.
+
+The observer is **fully opt-in**, gated by a single new coordination config
+flag `learning_difficulty_metrics` (bool, default `false`). When enabled, it
+persists its output as `artifacts/difficulty_metrics.json` alongside MassGen's
+existing coordination logs.
+
+## Motivation
+
+Today, propose-critique-vote runs in MassGen emit rich categorical telemetry
+(`AgentAnswer.content`, `AgentVote.voted_for`, `AgentVote.reason`) but no
+interpretable scalar summary of "how hard was this task for this team?" A
+post-run scalar enables three downstream capabilities:
+
+1. **Run-to-run comparability.** Operators currently compare runs by eyeballing
+   vote trajectories; TDI provides a compact 0-1 score.
+2. **Adaptive orchestration.** A future PR can use TDI as the target of a
+   Bayesian recommender that picks `(n_agents, n_rounds, backbones)` before
+   a full run — the multi-agent analogue of Snell et al. 2024's
+   compute-optimal per-prompt TTC allocation.
+3. **Evolving-skill creator signal.** The `evolving-skill-creator` skill can
+   consume TDI to prioritise skill evolution on harder tasks.
+
+## What counts as "difficulty" here
+
+We deliberately take the *group's own* dynamics — vote concentration,
+critique severity, round-over-round convergence — as the difficulty proxy.
+Concretely:
+
+- **ACE (Agent Confidence Entropy)** — normalised Shannon entropy of the
+  softmax-scaled per-agent vote-share distribution. Low = decisive hierarchy;
+  high = contested.
+- **CSD (Critique Severity Dispersion)** — variance of per-vote severities.
+  Severity is either the default *vote-share projection*
+  (sev = 1 − vote_share(target), deterministic, no LLM) or an injected
+  LLM-based rater that consumes `AgentVote.reason`. The LLM path complies
+  with MassGen's anti-pattern rule "no keyword/heuristic matching".
+- **WFR (Winner Flip Rate)** — fraction of consecutive rounds in which the
+  winner changed.
+- **TDI (Task Difficulty Index)** — convex combination of ACE, CSD,
+  lack-of-convergence, and WFR; weights sum to 1.0 and are configurable.
+
+## Design principles
+
+- **Zero new third-party dependencies.** Pure Python with `statistics` only.
+- **No orchestrator patching.** The observer is a consumer of the existing
+  `CoordinationTracker` event stream; the orchestrator simply calls
+  `observer.on_round_end(...)` once per round if the flag is enabled.
+- **Duck-typed on AgentAnswer / AgentVote.** We read only `agent_id`,
+  `voter_id`, `voted_for`, `reason` attributes — no new dataclass fields
+  are required.
+- **TDD.** Seven unit test classes ship with the PR; all assert a single
+  behaviour each.
+
+## Config surface (new fields under `orchestrator.coordination`)
+
+| Key | Type | Default | Purpose |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| `learning_difficulty_metrics` | bool | `false` | Turn the observer on. |
+| `learning_difficulty_metrics_ace_temperature` | float | `1.0` | ACE softmax $\tau$. |
+| `learning_difficulty_metrics_tdi_alpha_ace` | float | `0.35` | TDI coef for ACE. |
+| `learning_difficulty_metrics_tdi_beta_csd` | float | `0.25` | TDI coef for CSD. |
+| `learning_difficulty_metrics_tdi_gamma_lack_of_conv` | float | `0.25` | TDI coef for $(1 - \Delta C)$. |
+| `learning_difficulty_metrics_tdi_delta_wfr` | float | `0.15` | TDI coef for WFR. |
+
+Coefficients must sum to 1.0; the observer raises `ValueError` otherwise.
+
+## Files added
+
+- `massgen/learning/__init__.py`
+- `massgen/learning/difficulty_metrics.py`
+- `massgen/configs/learning/difficulty_metrics.yaml`
+- `massgen/tests/unit/test_difficulty_metrics.py`
+- `openspec/changes/add-difficulty-metrics/proposal.md` (this file)
+- `openspec/changes/add-difficulty-metrics/tasks.md`
+
+## Files modified (minimal surgical edits)
+
+Per the contract in `CLAUDE.md § Configuration`:
+
+1. `massgen/agent_config.py::CoordinationConfig` — six new fields with
+   sensible defaults.
+2. `massgen/agent_config.py::AgentConfig.to_dict()` — serialise the six
+   fields inside the existing `coordination_config` block.
+3. `massgen/cli.py::_parse_coordination_config()` — parse the six keys.
+
+No changes to `orchestrator.py`, `chat_agent.py`, any backend, or
+`coordination_tracker.py`.
+
+## Backwards compatibility
+
+The new flag defaults to `false`. Every existing YAML config continues to work
+unchanged; no existing field is renamed or removed.
+
+## Test plan
+
+- Unit tests assert per-round and run-level math on synthetic
+  `AgentAnswer`/`AgentVote` records (no LLM calls required).
+- Integration smoke test can be added in a follow-up PR that exercises the
+  flag via `uv run massgen --automation --config ... "…"` and asserts the
+  `artifacts/difficulty_metrics.json` file shape.
+
+## What's Next
+
+This PR adds the *measurement* layer. A follow-up OpenSpec proposal
+(`add-difficulty-recommender`) will use the same observer's output to
+power a Bayesian recommender over `(n_agents, n_rounds, backbones)`
+configurations, closing the loop on "spend compute adaptively".
